  "summary": "Malicious code in zetrix-development-utils (npm)",
  "details": "Package auto-dumps the host project's MongoDB database on require() without consent, by reading MONGODB_URI from the host's.env file and writing all collections to a local dump/ directory. It also exfiltrates data to a C2 endpoint at hxxps://auth[.]publicnode1[.]online/v2 via a POST with base64-encoded content, exposed through exported stringify() and randomBytes() functions. A real npm publish token is shipped in the package's.env file.",
